By Udora Orizu The Speaker of the House of Representatives Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila has expressed sadness over the passing away of former Governor of Kaduna State, Malam Abdulkadir Balarabe Musa. The Speaker, in a statement issued by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Lanre Lasisi, condoled with the government and people of Kaduna State over the loss. He described the late Balarabe Musa as a dogged democrat, who would be remembered for always standing for democracy. Gbajabiamila said the late politician was one Nigerian who could be described as highly patriotic in his dealings. While praying for the repose of his soul, the Speaker also prayed the Almighty to give his family the fortitude to bear the loss.